{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01Cn4C3kYKyU6skcbKzpJmDw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Looking at the problem: Shanille's free throw percentage starts below 80% and ends above 80%. We need to show it must equal exactly 80% at some point. The answer is \"yes\".\n\nThe proof: Let $f(N) = 5S(N) - 4N$. Then $f$ starts negative, ends positive, and changes by $-4$ or $+1$ each step. So at the last $N$ where $f \\le 0$, we have $f \\le 0$ and the next step jumps up, requiring the increment of $+1$, which means $f$ went from $\\le 0$ to $> 0$ via $+1$, so it was exactly $0$."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":328,"cache_read_input_tokens":26657,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":328},"output_tokens":69,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4bf2cfed-ef9e-4d08-b64a-fa47bb9d2f25","uuid":"0ec29587-deac-46c5-8580-a0b898af6852"}
